                                                          way of handling words and expressing things: it rearranges the world of letters. Dyslexia is not always
                                                          immediately apparent—until it emerges—a neabry way of spelling. With mining meisspelling this work looks at
                                                          the histroy of how English is standardised and the imperialsisms that determine normative ways of spelking,
                                                          spelling, and articuilating. It puts the experience of dyslexia at the centre and takes veissitors through the
